This paper discusses the vulnerabilities and potential attacks on Medical Imaging Devices (MIDs) and their infrastructure, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on the impact of these attacks on patient health, which is related to the field of healthcare (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of protocols and standards such as DICOM and HL7, which are related to the field of cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). The paper also mentions the risk analysis survey conducted to identify the characteristics of cyber-attacks, which is related to the field of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the potential disruption of digital images, which is related to the field of signal processing (cs.SI).
